The paper deals with randomized query complexity, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). It also introduces a new lower bound measure called randomized sabotage complexity, which is related to data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses implications for lifting theorems in communication complexity, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
